<subSubSection id="20BC6569FFD529797043E51C3B7EFCC4" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="681936E2FFD529797043E51C3B7EFCC4" blockId="2.[136,1059,609,859]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">
Four ♂, 
<specimenCount id="7EA0FD6BFFD529797027E51C3A8DFDE4" box="[634,702,609,635]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" type="female">two ♀</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="7EA0FD6BFFD5297970AFE51C3BB7FDE4" box="[754,900,611,635]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
of unspecified sex (
<specimenCount id="7EA0FD6BFFD52979735BE5F9392FFD04" box="[262,284,641,667]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
?) are probably 
<typeStatus id="B71D8840FFD52979739CE5FC3A2DFD03" box="[449,542,644,668]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">syntypes</typeStatus>
(box 6). 
<materialsCitation id="D8CE3CBFFFD529797020E5FC399AFD24" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">
Two ♂ and 
<specimenCount id="7EA0FD6BFFD5297970A7E5FC3B0EFD04" box="[762,829,641,667]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" type="female">one ♀</specimenCount>
labelled: &quot;[sex] 
<collectingCountry id="10B17672FFD5297971B7E5FB3C11FD04" box="[1002,1058,643,667]" name="Cuba" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Cuba</collectingCountry>
<collectorName id="C5535334FFD529797289E5DC39ADFD24" box="[212,414,675,699]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">M. H. de Saussure</collectorName>
&quot;
</materialsCitation>
, 
<materialsCitation id="D8CE3CBFFFD5297973E5E5DC3BD1FD44" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">
two ♂ and 
<specimenCount id="7EA0FD6BFFD52979706AE5DC3A4FFD24" box="[567,636,673,699]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" type="female">one ♀</specimenCount>
labelled: &quot;[sex] 
<collectingCountry id="10B17672FFD52979716FE5DB3B59FD24" box="[818,874,675,699]" name="Cuba" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(Mr.) 
<location id="6D796039FFD5297971EEE5DC3BDBFD23" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:E00F87F4FFD5297972D5E51B3B7EFCC4:6D796039FFD5297971EEE5DC3BDBFD23" box="[947,1000,676,700]" country="Cuba" name="Poey" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Poey</location>
&quot; and the unspecified specimen: &quot;75- 
<specimenCount id="7EA0FD6BFFD529797076E5BB3A69FD44" box="[555,602,705,731]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" type="female">2 ♀</specimenCount>
= 5-23 
<taxonomicName id="AFA64D61FFD5297970E6E5BB3BE4FD44" authority="Sauss." authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1869" box="[699,983,707,731]" class="Insecta" family="Liturgusidae" genus="Gonatista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cubensis">Gonatista cubensis Sauss.</taxonomicName>
&quot;
</materialsCitation>
Each specimen has also a label &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="AFA64D61FFD5297973A5E59B3AD0FD64" authority="Fabr." authorityName="Fabr." box="[504,739,739,763]" class="Insecta" family="Liturgusidae" genus="Gonatista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grisea">Gonatista grisea Fabr.</taxonomicName>
&quot; (green paper). All labels are handwritten. 
<taxonomicName id="AFA64D61FFD52979733FE47C39D3FC84" authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1869" box="[354,480,771,795]" class="Insecta" family="Liturgusidae" genus="Gonatista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cubensis">
<emphasis id="5AD2EAF0FFD52979733FE47C39D3FC84" box="[354,480,771,795]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">G. cubensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is now considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="AFA64D61FFD5297971C4E47C39A3FCA4" authority="(Thunberg, 1815)" baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1815" class="Insecta" family="Liturgusidae" genus="Gonatista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis id="5AD2EAF0FFD5297971C4E47C3C10FC84" box="[921,1059,771,795]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">G. reticulata</emphasis>
(Thunberg, 1815)
</taxonomicName>
, but Saussure &amp; Zehntner (1894) placed it in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="AFA64D61FFD529797289E43C39C4FCC4" authority="(Fabricius, 1793)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[212,503,835,859]" class="Insecta" family="Liturgusidae" genus="Gonatista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grisea">
<emphasis id="5AD2EAF0FFD529797289E43C390BFCC4" box="[212,312,836,859]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">G. grisea</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1793)
</taxonomicName>
, hence the identification labels.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
